main event: On June 3, 1953, Mrs. C.H. Warren observed a very bright light in the southern sky near Muster, Texas, which appeared to be diving and climbing at a rapid rate of speed. She observed the object for approximately 15 minutes.
interesting points: The object was observed at an altitude of approximately 300 feet.
Mrs. Warren was quite disturbed by the incident and believed it was some type of unidentified aerial object.
Mrs. Warren was not hysterical and was very concerned about notifying the proper authorities.
The Air Force requested more information on the sighting, including details of the observation, reliability of the observers, and any physical objects that could have caused the sighting.
The report mentions a follow-up request for additional information to be provided to Project Blue Book.
sighted object: A very bright light in the sky
